revision.text:
'''善光寺街道'''（ぜんこうじかいどう）とは、京阪や江戸から[[善光寺]]参拝に向かう道。
*[[北国街道 (信越)]] - [[上越市|直江津]]から[[追分宿|追分]]までの北国街道。
*[[北国西街道]] - [[中山道]]洗馬から[[北国街道 (信越)|北国街道]]丹波島までの脇往還。

{{Aimai}}
{{デフォルトソート:せんこうしかいとう}}

'''善光寺街道'''（ぜんこうじかいどう）とは、京阪や江戸から[[善光寺]]参拝に向かう道。
*[[北国街道 (信越)|北国街道]] ： [[上越市|直江津]]から[[追分宿|追分]]までの北国街道。
*[[北国西街道]] ： [[中山道]]洗馬から[[北国街道 (信越)|北国街道]]丹波島までの脇往還。

{{Aimai}}
{{デフォルトソート:せんこうしかいとう}}

'''善光寺街道'''（ぜんこうじかいどう）とは、京阪や江戸から[[善光寺]]参拝に向かう道。
*[[北国街道 (信越)|北国街道]]：[[上越市|直江津]]から[[追分宿|追分]]までの北国街道。
*[[北国西街道]]：[[中山道]]洗馬から北国街道丹波島までの脇往還。

{{Aimai}}
{{デフォルトソート:せんこうしかいとう}}

'''善光寺街道'''（ぜんこうじかいどう）とは、京阪や江戸から[[善光寺]]参拝に向かう道。
*[[北国街道 (信越)|北国街道]]：[[上越市|直江津]]から[[追分宿|追分]]までの北国街道。
*[[北国西街道]]：[[中山道]]洗馬から北国街道[[丹波島宿]]までの脇往還。

{{Aimai}}
{{デフォルトソート:せんこうしかいとう}}

'''Zenkoji Highways''' (善光寺街道) is not an official name for a specific road but a common term used to refer to routes frequently traveled by pilgrims visiting {{ill|Zenkoji|ja|善光寺}}. As such, multiple routes are referred to by this name:

* {{ill|Hokkokukaido (Shinetsu)|ja|北国街道 (信越)}}  
  : A branch route of the {{ill|Nakasendo|ja|中山道}}, starting at {{ill|Oiwake-shuku|ja|追分宿}} in {{ill|Karuizawa|ja|軽井沢町}}, Nagano Prefecture, and extending to {{ill|Takada Castle|ja|高田城}} in {{ill|Joetsu|ja|上越市}}, Niigata Prefecture. Pilgrims from Edo or the Kanto region would travel via Nakasendo and branch off at Oiwake-shuku to reach Zenkoji. Pilgrims from the coastal regions of the Sea of Japan would start their journey southward from Takada.

* {{ill|Hokkokunishikaido|ja|北国西街道}}  
  : A branch route of the Nakasendo starting at {{ill|Shiomashuku|ja|洗馬宿}} in {{ill|Shiojiri|ja|塩尻市}}, Nagano Prefecture, and joining the Hokkokukaido at {{ill|Tanbashimashuku|ja|丹波島宿}} in {{ill|Nagano City|ja|長野市}}. This route, also known as Zenkoji West Highway, was primarily used by pilgrims from Kyoto, Osaka, and other western regions traveling via the Nakasendo.

* {{ill|Tokamachi Highway|ja|十日町街道}} / {{ill|Tani Highway|ja|谷街道}}  
  : This route runs from {{ill|Ojiya-shuku|ja|小千谷宿}} in {{ill|Ojiya|ja|小千谷市}}, Niigata Prefecture, to the castle town of {{ill|Iiyama Castle|ja|飯山城}} in {{ill|Iiyama|ja|飯山市}}, Nagano Prefecture, where it connects to the Tani Highway. It continues via the castle town of {{ill|Matsushiro Castle|ja|松代城}} to Zenkoji. Pilgrims from northern coastal regions, especially from Chūetsu and beyond, commonly used this route.

{{Aimai}}
[[ja:善光寺街道]]
[[Category:Japanese highways]]
[[Category:Nagano Prefecture]]
[[Category:Historical roads in Japan]]

