'''Zenkoji Highways''' (善光寺街道) is not an official name for a specific road but a common term used to refer to routes frequently traveled by pilgrims visiting [[:en:Zenkō-ji|Zenkoji]]. As such, multiple routes are referred to by this name:

* [[:en:Hokkoku_Kaidō|Hokkoku Kaidō]]
** A branch route of the [[:en:Nakasendō|Nakasendo]], starting at [[:en:Oiwake-shuku|Oiwake-shuku]] in [[:en:Karuizawa, Nagano|Karuizawa]], Nagano Prefecture, and extending to [[:en:Takada Castle|Takada Castle]] in [[:en:Jōetsu, Niigata|Joetsu]], Niigata Prefecture. Pilgrims from Edo or the Kanto region would travel via Nakasendo and branch off at Oiwake-shuku to reach Zenkoji. Pilgrims from the coastal regions of the Sea of Japan would start their journey southward from Takada.

* {{ill|Hokkokunishikaido|ja|北国西街道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokkokunishikaido|qq=|1=Hokkokunishikaido|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11401310}}
** A branch route of the Nakasendo starting at [[:en:Seba-juku|Shiomashuku]] in [[:en:Shiojiri, Nagano|Shiojiri]], Nagano Prefecture, and joining the Hokkokukaido at {{ill|Tanbashimashuku|ja|丹波島宿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanbashimashuku|qq=}} in [[:en:Nagano (city)|Nagano City]]. This route, also known as Zenkoji West Highway, was primarily used by pilgrims from Kyoto, Osaka, and other western regions traveling via the Nakasendo.

* {{ill|Tokamachi Highway|ja|十日町街道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokamachi Highway|qq=|1=Tokamachi Highway|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q133947489}} / {{ill|Tani Highway|ja|谷街道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tani Highway|qq=|1=Tani Highway|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11633097}}
** This route runs from {{ill|Ojiya-shuku|ja|小千谷宿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ojiya-shuku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Ojiya, Niigata|Ojiya]], Niigata Prefecture, to the castle town of [[:en:Iiyama Castle|Iiyama Castle]] in [[:en:Iiyama, Nagano|Iiyama]], Nagano Prefecture, where it connects to the Tani Highway. It continues via the castle town of [[:en:Matsushiro Castle|Matsushiro Castle]] to Zenkoji. Pilgrims from northern coastal regions, especially from Chūetsu and beyond, commonly used this route.
